She's very reliant on her constructs (robots) for extremely menial tasks like taking away objects as small as a smartphone, and whether because of her natural ability to apparate outside of her physical body and into other objects or because she's become so ingrained in being surrounded by inorganic, sentient beings, she takes being dead as just a minor inconvenience. By the time she's become infirm due to events in the game, that point is further emphasized.

Despite this, she's very thoughtful, hates the idea of someone she's known only a short time suffering a tragic fate and it's her suggestion that ultimately leads to the game's conclusion.
